# Ruled Prompt Module Guidance

- Keep ruled prompt UI logic in `cockatrice/src/game/prompt/game_prompt_widget.{h,cpp}`.
- Keep `TabGame` responsible for placement and signal wiring only.
- The prompt should live in the right-side `Messages` dock above the game log for ruled games.
- Do not create a separate prompt dock/window unless explicitly requested.
- Reuse existing command paths: `Pass Priority` should trigger `GameEventHandler::handleNextTurn()`.
- Preserve mode safety:
  - ruled prompt visible only in ruled non-replay games
  - no behavior changes for legacy freeform/replay paths
- Prefer consuming existing signals (`logRuledEngine`, `logActivePhaseChanged`, `logActivePlayer`) instead of adding new protocol events for UI text.
- Keep prompt widget compact and action-first; reserve space for future action buttons without wiring unsupported actions.

## Quick check before finishing

- Build `cockatrice` target and verify compile success.
- Confirm prompt remains above the message log in the right sidebar.
- Confirm `Pass Priority` behavior still maps to ruled pass-priority command flow.
